Settlement Conferences (MSC)
Remote appearance is mandatory
Parties that appear in person will be provided a public laptop in the courtroom
The Family Law Commissioner will hear Family Law Status Conferences
Zoom Credentials are available on the Family Law Commissioner’s webpage

The judicial officer conferencing the matter will host the Zoom conference
Requests for Order (RFO)
Remote or in-person appearances are allowed
Remote appearances are authorized for case parties and attorneys related to the case
Request for Order Calendars are part of the Family Law Direct Calendaring system
Please find the Zoom Credentials by viewing the assigned Judicial Officer’s webpage at Family Law Direct Calendaring | Superior Court of California | County of San Mateo
Domestic Violence Prevention Act-Temporary Restraining Order (DVPA/TRO)
Remote or in-person appearances are allowed
Remote appearances are authorized for case parties and attorneys related to the case
A DVPA/TRO matter may be heard by a Commissioner or by a Family Law Direct Department
If your matter is assigned to a Commissioner, please find Zoom Credentials on the Family Law Commissioner's webpage
If your matter is assigned to a Direct Department, please find the Zoom Credentials by viewing the assigned Judicial Officer’s webpage at Family Law Direct Calendaring | Superior Court of California | County of San Mateo
If the matter proceeds to a hearing, the hearing may be conducted remotely or in-person.

PLEASE TAKE ...
data.title:
Procedure Requirement
Tentative Rulings

data.full_text:
Tentative Rulings
PLEASE TAKE NOTICE that tentative rulings on Law & Motion matters will continue to be posted by 3:00 p.

data.label: tentative ruling will continue...
data.title:
Procedure Requirement
tentative ruling will continue to be required by 4:00 p.
data.full_text: tentative ruling will continue to be required by 4:00 p.

data.label: A party intending to appear in...
data.title:
Compliance Requirement
A party intending to appear in order to contest the tentative ruling on a matter calendared for hearing must notify the assigned Judge's Department by 4:00 p.
data.full_text: A party intending to appear in order to contest the tentative ruling on a matter calendared for hearing must notify the assigned Judge's Department by 4:00 p.

data.label: ) Any email to the Court must ...
data.title:
Compliance Requirement
) Any email to the Court must be contemporaneously copied to all parties or their counsel of record.
data.full_text: ) Any email to the Court must be contemporaneously copied to all parties or their counsel of record.

data.label: ) Emails contesting the tentat...
data.title:
Compliance Requirement
) Emails contesting the tentative ruling must state the case name and number in the subject line.
data.full_text: ) Emails contesting the tentative ruling must state the case name and number in the subject line.

data.label: In the email the contesting pa...
data.title:
Compliance Requirement
In the email the contesting party must include the name of the motion, the party contesting, and the time estimate for oral arguments.
data.full_text: In the email the contesting party must include the name of the motion, the party contesting, and the time estimate for oral arguments.

data.label: Emails must be in at least 12 ...
data.title:
Compliance Requirement
Emails must be in at least 12 point type.
data.full_text: Emails must be in at least 12 point type.

data.label: Parties intending to appear an...
data.title:
Compliance Requirement
Parties intending to appear and contest the tentative ruling must notify both the Court and opposing counsel of such intent by 4:00 p.
data.full_text: Parties intending to appear and contest the tentative ruling must notify both the Court and opposing counsel of such intent by 4:00 p.

data.label: You must appear at the hearing...
data.title:
Compliance Requirement
You must appear at the hearing if you are so directed by the Court in the tentative ruling and be prepared to address those issues set forth by the Court in that ruling.
data.full_text: You must appear at the hearing if you are so directed by the Court in the tentative ruling and be prepared to address those issues set forth by the Court in that ruling.

data.label: Unless the Court and opposing ...
data.title:
Compliance Requirement
Unless the Court and opposing counsel have been notified of such intent, the tentative ruling shall become the ruling of the Court without oral argument.
data.full_text: Unless the Court and opposing counsel have been notified of such intent, the tentative ruling shall become the ruling of the Court without oral argument.

data.label: the prior court day, and notic...
data.title:
Compliance Requirement
the prior court day, and notice of appearance to contest a tentative ruling will continue to be required by 4:00 p.
data.full_text: the prior court day, and notice of appearance to contest a tentative ruling will continue to be required by 4:00 p.

data.title:

Standing Orders 
 
 All standing orders of the Superior Court shall be signed by the Presiding Judge, shall (unless 
otherwise noted) specify each is in effect indefinitely until vacated or superseded by the Presiding Judge, 
shall be numbered sequentially and filed chronologically by the Clerk in a special file marked “Standing 
Orders”, shall be distributed to all judicial officers of the court and shall be published by the San Mateo 
County Bar Association as an appendix to the Local Rules of the Superior Court at such times as the 
Local Rules are published.

data.full_text: All inquiries and complaints lodged against a panel member must be submitted in writing to the Court’s ADR Administrator, who shall serve as the complaint coordinator pursuant to CRC §3.

data.label: All complaint procedures and c...
data.title:
Compliance Requirement
All complaint procedures and complaint proceedings shall be kept confidential.
data.full_text: All complaint procedures and complaint proceedings shall be kept confidential.

data.label: Upon receipt of a complaint, t...
data.title:
Compliance Requirement
Upon receipt of a complaint, the ADR Administrator shall send the complainant a confidential written acknowledgment that the Court has received the complaint.
data.full_text: Upon receipt of a complaint, the ADR Administrator shall send the complainant a confidential written acknowledgment that the Court has received the complaint.

data.label: If the complaint is not resolv...
data.title:
Compliance Requirement
If the complaint is not resolved or closed pursuant to this preliminary review: (1) The mediator shall be given written notice of the complaint and an opportunity to respond.
data.full_text: If the complaint is not resolved or closed pursuant to this preliminary review: (1) The mediator shall be given written notice of the complaint and an opportunity to respond.

data.label: (2) The complaint shall be inv...
data.title:
Compliance Requirement
(2) The complaint shall be investigated and a written recommendation concerning court action on the complaint shall be made by a complaint committee, to be appointed by the Presiding Judge.
data.full_text: (2) The complaint shall be investigated and a written recommendation concerning court action on the complaint shall be made by a complaint committee, to be appointed by the Presiding Judge.

data.label: (4) The Court shall send confi...
data.title:
Compliance Requirement
(4) The Court shall send confidential written notice of the final action taken by the court on the complaint to the complainant and to the mediator.
data.full_text: (4) The Court shall send confidential written notice of the final action taken by the court on the complaint to the complainant and to the mediator.
